<paragraph blockId="8.[189,349,1085,1114]" box="[189,349,1085,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,349,1085,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,917,1137,1199]" box="[234,378,1137,1164]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1137,1163]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Male</emphasis>
(n=2)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,917,1137,1199]" box="[189,917,1172,1199]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">
Length: 
<quantity box="[288,388,1173,1199]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 mm</quantity>
. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[553,684,1172,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[553,684,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">D. phoenix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[691,782,1173,1199]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1401,1238,1546]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">
Head with 7–9 well-developed frontal setae reaching level of apex of pedicel; acrostichals 3 (weakly differentiated) +1; intra-alars 2+2, meral setae 7–9; 
<collectionCode box="[822,840,1273,1299]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">T</collectionCode>
4 with 2–3 pairs of lateral marginal setae; row of about 12 marginal setae on 
<collectionCode box="[570,591,1308,1335]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">T</collectionCode>
5; inner margin of ST5 without lobes or incision (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1305,1308,1334]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); cercal prong truncated in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[577,672,1343,1370]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); surstylus slightly curved (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1101,1343,1370]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); pregonite 1.5× as long as postgonite (
<figureCitation box="[365,462,1379,1405]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); postgonite with long seta inserted near slightly dilated region in anteroapical corner (
<figureCitation box="[284,381,1414,1440]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); vesica X-shaped in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[807,900,1414,1440]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); juxta strongly projected towards ventral surface in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[470,566,1449,1475]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); median stylus narrow, as long as lateral stylus and with apical spines (
<figureCitation box="[198,330,1484,1510]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4D–E</figureCitation>
); lateral stylus with base twisted towards ventral margin of paraphallus and with apical spines (
<figureCitation box="[278,406,1519,1546]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[235,1337,289,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823740/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4D–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
